---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="about — goldfang" description="who is goldfang">
  <h1>about</h1>

  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      i build things that run on bare metal and talk over wireguard. most of my
      work lives at the intersection of systems programming, networking, and
      making my own tools because nothing else does the job right.
    </p>

    <p>
      primary stack: <code>rust</code>, <code>go</code>, <code>python</code>,
      linux, systemd. i like small binaries, clean init files, and
      machines that do exactly what they're told.
    </p>

    <h2>what i care about</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>self-hosting and owning your infrastructure</li>
      <li>minimal, composable tools over bloated frameworks</li>
      <li>building things that respect the machine they run on</li>
      <li>apt repos that actually work</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>setup</h2>
    <p>
      ubuntu 26.04 daily driver. everything deploys via github actions
      to github pages. no servers to babysit.
    </p>

    <h2>this site</h2>
    <p>
      static site built with astro. no runtime dependencies, no javascript
      bloat. the source lives at
      <a href="https://github.com/realgoldfang/realgoldfang.github.io">github</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .prose p:first-of-type { font-size: 1.05rem; }
</style>
